      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal grid convergence study with Richardson extrapolation and GCI reported for hemolysis QoI at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Three-level grid convergence study performed; GCI computed for velocity and pressure. Hemolysis index GCI exceeds 8% on finest grid, indicating insufficient discretization convergence for absolute hemolysis prediction. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match VAD operating envelope with documented uncertainty in flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid properties at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments conducted at 3 of 5 required operating points. Two high-speed operating conditions lack experimental data. Fluid property uncertainty partially documented. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted vs. measured hemolysis index with statistical metrics and uncertainty bands at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index compared to experimental measurements at 3 operating points. Mean absolute error of 35% observed. No formal hypothesis testing or confidence interval overlap analysis performed. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated that CFD-predicted hemolysis index is the direct QoI used in the clinical acceptance decision at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary QoI and directly maps to clinical threshold. Sensitivity analysis shows hemolysis prediction strongly dependent on model form assumptions not fully validated. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must cover the full VAD operating envelope including worst-case hemolysis conditions at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used FDA generic pump geometry, which differs from the specific VAD impeller geometry. Operating conditions cover partial envelope only. Extrapolation to full VAD envelope not validated. Gradation 2 achieved."
