      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documentation of analyst training, setup review, and independent verification of model configuration at Gradation 4 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "No formal use error assessment was conducted. Analyst qualifications and independent review of boundary condition setup were not documented. This factor was not assessed and constitutes an epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of turbulence model selection and hemolysis constitutive model form with sensitivity analysis at Gradation 5 for MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) was selected without systematic comparison to alternative model forms. Turbulence model sensitivity not evaluated. Model form uncertainty not quantified. Factor not assessed — epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in hemolysis model coefficients and blood rheological parameters must be propagated through Monte Carlo analysis at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Although Monte Carlo UQ was performed on geometric and flow boundary conditions, the hemolysis model empirical coefficients (C, alpha, beta) were held fixed at literature values without uncertainty characterization. Input uncertainty for these parameters was not assessed — epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Characterization of blood analog fluid properties and lot-to-lot variability in experimental samples at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data from FDA pump studies used porcine blood without documentation of hematocrit variability, storage conditions, or lot-to-lot differences. Sample characterization was not assessed — epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that CFD boundary conditions match experimental inlet/outlet conditions within documented tolerances at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles prescribed as uniform rather than measured profiles. Outlet pressure boundary conditions assumed atmospheric without experimental confirmation. Equivalency between simulation inputs and experimental conditions not rigorously established. Gradation 2 achieved."
